body: [[[#entityType16956668845560]]] also known as the Dark Knight, is a symbol of justice and vengeance in the crime-ridden Gotham City. He witnessed his parents' murder as a child, driving him to dedicate his life to fighting crime and ensuring that no one suffers the same fate he endured. Clad in a bat-themed suit and armed with an array of cutting-edge technology, he utilizes his exceptional intellect, martial arts skills, and detective abilities to combat both street-level thugs and formidable villains.

body: [[[#entityType16956671009060]]] the Man of Steel, is a symbol of hope and strength. Clark Kent, his alter ego, conceals his immense powers while upholding justice and defending the innocent. Raised with moral values, he fights for truth, justice, and the greater good, embodying the best of humanity with a touch of the extraordinary.

body: [[[#entityType16956673183820]]], aka Peter Parker, is a relatable hero navigating the complexities of being a teenager while shouldering immense responsibilities. After a radioactive spider bite grants him powers, he grapples with guilt over his uncle's death, learning that "with great power comes great responsibility." Balancing personal struggles with crime-fighting, he swings through New York, embodying resilience, quick wit, and a desire to make the world a better place.

body: [[[#entityType16956693261410]]], the "Merc with a Mouth," is an antihero known for his irreverent humor, regenerative healing factor, and breaking the fourth wall. Wade Wilson, scarred and with a twisted sense of justice, embraces his Deadpool persona. Merciless and unpredictable, he takes on contracts while making pop culture references and keeping readers and viewers entertained with his unique brand of chaos. Despite the chaos, there's an underlying complexity to his character, showcasing the struggle between his humanity and the harsh reality he faces.
